{{Infobox artist | bgcolour = #6495ED | name = Dobrosav Milojević | image = | imagesize = 288px | caption = Dobrosav in 2005 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1948|12|24|df=y}} | birth_place = Jagodina, Serbia | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Serbian | field = Painting | training = Museum of Naïve and Marginal Art<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.naiveart.rs/iz13.htm |title=Dobrosav Milojević at the Museum of Naïve and Marginal Art in Jagodina |publisher=Naiveart.rs |date= |accessdate=2012-07-31 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100406084356/http://www.naiveart.rs/iz13.htm |archivedate=2010-04-06 |df= }}</ref> in [[Jagodina]] | movement = [[Naïve art]] | works = | patrons = | influenced by = | influenced = | awards = ˝Grand prix of the Biennal of [[Naïve art]]˝ }}
'''Dobrosav Milojević''' was born in Donje Štiplje near [[Jagodina]] in 1948. He is well-known living Serbian artist among the [[Naïve painters]]. Now, he lives and works in Donje Štiplje.
== Biography == The official start of his dealing with the naive art is since 1971, when he was admitted to the Museum of Naïve and Marginal Art in [[Jagodina]]. Since then, he is its constant member. In the last 40 years, he had a huge number of solo exhibitions in [[Serbia]] and around the world. He has a permanent exhibition of paintings in the Museum of Naive Art in Jagodina and his paintings can be seen in many galleries around the world: Museum of Naïve and Marginal Art, Gallery of Self-taught Artists in Trebnje, the Galleries in Sanski Most, Gallery of International Naïve Art (GINA)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ginagallery.com/Gallery/ShowArtistItems.asp?ArtistId=90 |title=Dobrosav´s paintings in Gallery of International Naïve Art (GINA) |publisher=Ginagallery.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-31}}</ref> in [[Tel Aviv]], Gallery of Naive Art in [[Kovačica (town)|Kovačica]], Gallery of Primitive and Folk Art, San Francisco. He has won several awards and plaques for his work.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.naiveart.rs/iz13.htm |title=About Dobrosav Milojević´s awards at the Museum of Naïve and Marginal Art in Jagodina |publisher=Naiveart.rs |date= |accessdate=2012-07-31 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100406084356/http://www.naiveart.rs/iz13.htm |archivedate=2010-04-06 |df= }}</ref>
==Art== He was interested in painting since early boyhood. As a child of the village he found inspiration in motifs that are related to village and life in it. While he lived in the city he felt strong nostalgie for the village and happy childhood days. This resulted in many of vividly pictures that depicted a beautiful landscape of mountains around the [[Crni Vrh (Jagodina)]], the mountain that marked his life and which he finally returned. Among the many affirmative opinions about his painting, the most important are: * former President of the [[Serbian Academy of Sciences and Arts]] Dr. [[Dejan Medaković]]´s opinion<ref>See Dr. Dejan Medaković's opinion on the - [https://archive.is/20120905202548/http://www.ogledalovu.com/izdavastvo/milojevic.html Ogledalo vizuelne umetnosti] and [http://www.naiveart.rs/iz13.htm Dobrosav Milojević at the Museum of Naïve and Marginal Art in Jagodina] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100406084356/http://www.naiveart.rs/iz13.htm |date=April 6, 2010 }}</ref> (from the Dobrosav Milojević's Catalogue, Museum of Naïve Art, Jagodina, 1997), * and Member of Department of Language and Literature of [[Serbian Academy of Sciences and Arts]] Dr. Vojislav J. Đurić´s opinion<ref>See Dr. Vojislav J. Đurić's opinion on the - [https://archive.is/20120905202548/http://www.ogledalovu.com/izdavastvo/milojevic.html Ogledalo vizuelne umetnosti] and [http://www.naiveart.rs/iz13.htm Dobrosav Milojević at the Museum of Naïve and Marginal Art in Jagodina] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100406084356/http://www.naiveart.rs/iz13.htm |date=April 6, 2010 }})</ref> (from speech at the opening of exhibition in Jagodina, 8 December 1993).
